Document: RDTextureFormat
Path: godot/classes/class_rdtextureformat.rst
Summary: Describes the RDTextureFormat enumeration used by RenderingDevice.

RDTextureFormat is an enumeration used by RenderingDevice.
---CHUNK---
Document: RDTextureFormat
Path: godot/classes/class_rdtextureformat.rst
Summary: Defines the properties of a texture format used by the RenderingDevice.

Properties:
- array_layers (int): Number of layers in the texture array. Default: 1
- depth (int): Depth of the texture (for 3D textures or texture arrays). Default: 1
- format (DataFormat): The pixel format of the texture. Default: 8
- height (int): Height of the texture. Default: 1
- is_discardable (bool): Whether the texture can be discarded when not in use. Default: false
- is_resolve_buffer (bool): Whether the texture is used as a resolve buffer for multisampling. Default: false
- mipmaps (int): Number of mipmaps for the texture. Default: 1
- samples (TextureSamples): Number of samples for multisampling. Default: 0
- texture_type (TextureType): The type of the texture (e.g., 2D, 3D, array). Default: 1
- usage_bits (TextureUsageBits): Bitfield specifying how the texture will be used. Default: 0
- width (int): Width of the texture. Default: 1
---CHUNK---
Document: RDTextureFormat
Path: godot/classes/class_rdtextureformat.rst
Summary: Methods for managing shareable texture formats within the RenderingDevice.

Method: add_shareable_format(format: DataFormat) → void
Adds a `DataFormat` to the list of shareable formats.

Method: remove_shareable_format(format: DataFormat) → void
Removes a `DataFormat` from the list of shareable formats.
