Document: RDTextureFormat
Path: godot/classes/class_rdtextureformat.rst
Summary: Describes the properties and member variables of the RDTextureFormat class, which define the characteristics of a texture used in the RenderingDevice.

Property: array_layers (int)
Description: The number of layers in the texture. Only relevant for 2D texture arrays.
Default: 1
Setter: set_array_layers
Getter: get_array_layers

Property: depth (int)
Description: The texture's depth (in pixels). This is always 1 for 2D textures.
Default: 1
Setter: set_depth
Getter: get_depth

Property: format (DataFormat)
Description: The texture's pixel data format.
Default: 8
Setter: set_format
Getter: get_format

Property: height (int)
Description: The texture's height (in pixels).
Default: 1
Setter: set_height
Getter: get_height

Property: is_discardable (bool)
Description: If a texture is discardable, its contents do not need to be preserved between frames. This flag is only relevant when the texture is used as target in a draw list. This information is used by RenderingDevice to figure out if a texture's contents can be discarded, eliminating unnecessary writes to memory and boosting performance.
Default: false
Setter: set_is_discardable
Getter: get_is_discardable

Property: is_resolve_buffer (bool)
Description: The texture will be used as the destination of a resolve operation.
Default: false
Setter: set_is_resolve_buffer
Getter: get_is_resolve_buffer

Property: mipmaps (int)
Description: The number of mipmaps available in the texture.
Default: 1
Setter: set_mipmaps
Getter: get_mipmaps

Property: samples (TextureSamples)
Description: The number of samples used when sampling the texture.
Default: 0
Setter: set_samples
Getter: get_samples

Property: texture_type (TextureType)
Description: The texture type.
Default: 1
Setter: set_texture_type
Getter: get_texture_type

Property: usage_bits (bitfield[TextureUsageBits])
Description: The texture's usage bits, which determine what can be done using the texture.
Default: 0
Setter: set_usage_bits
Getter: get_usage_bits

Property: width (int)
Description: The texture's width (in pixels).
Default: 1
Setter: set_width
Getter: get_width
---CHUNK---
Document: RDTextureFormat
Path: godot/classes/class_rdtextureformat.rst
Summary: Describes methods for managing shareable texture formats within the RenderingDevice.
Method: add_shareable_format(format: DataFormat) → void
Adds format as a valid format for the corresponding RDTextureView's format_override property. If any format is added as shareable, then the main format must also be added.
Method: remove_shareable_format(format: DataFormat) → void
Removes format from the list of valid formats that the corresponding RDTextureView's format_override property can be set to.